narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned a lot about calculus taking this class. It was a good continuation of calc 1.
This course taught me the essential components of integral calculus, building upon my knowledge of differential calculus.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Fun material but less than half the class show up regularly.
Strengths were that there were many resources available to succeed in the course

This class is taught and organized very well. Everything on the Canvas page is clear and easy to understand, as is the syllabus. You know what is expected of you as a student and it helps a lot in trying to organize how you go about this class. As well, the support is amazing in Math 115. There are peer tutors, office hours, and tons of review sessions before exams. They give you a lot of support and it really helps when it comes to problems sets, midterms, and finals.
This course was overly complicated in its processes and often felt more difficult than it should have. I felt more confused leaving office hours/discussion sections that I had going into them.
This course provides excellent online resources for better understanding the material.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: I would recommend this course to another student, especially if they are interested in math. Math 115 isn't too difficult, but it will definitely challenge you and make you think about math in different ways.
